]<answer>By the Rational Root Theorem, the only real roots of this polynomial are $\pm 1$.  Then $-1$ works, so by polynomial long division $(x+1)$ is a factor of $x^4+x^3+x+1$.  Then $x^4+x^3+x+1=(x+1)(x^3+1)=(x+1)^2(x^2-x+1)$.  Thus, we have factored $x^4+x^3+x+1=(x+1)^2(x^2-x+1)$, all with real coefficients.</answer>

