\[\frac{1}{z} = \frac{1}{w} = \frac{1}{r \operatorname{cis} \theta} = \frac{1}{r} \operatorname{cis} (-\theta) = \frac{\cos \theta - i \sin \theta}{r},\]so $\frac{\cos \theta}{r} = \frac{1}{2},$ or $r = 2 \cos \theta.$

